<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Wake2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Wake,</orth> vb. (impf. and partic. <emph>--d</emph>) 1) trans. to rouse from sleep: <bibl n="shak. ven 855" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 855</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 942" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 942</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.312" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 312</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.49.312" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 132</bibl> (<emph>to w. our peace;</emph> cf. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.139.132" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.288" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 288</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 98</bibl>. See <emph>Awake</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.261" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 261</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 1, 85</bibl> (Ff <emph>awaked</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 2, 24</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 55</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.7.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.258" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 258</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.9.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 9, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.323" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 323</bibl>. Metaphorically, == to arouse, to excite, to put in action: <cit><quote>she --s her heart by beating on her breast,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 759" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 759</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we will not w. your patience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 102</bibl></cit> (cf. <cit><quote>to w. our peace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 132</bibl></cit>; and see <emph>Awake</emph>). <cit><quote>upon his aid to w. Northumberland,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.6.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 6, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to w. and wage a danger profitless,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>answer my --d wrath,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.363" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 363</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) refl. to be awakened: <cit><quote>--d herself with laughing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.361" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 361</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he will . . . find Hector's purpose pointing on him, and w. him to the answer,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.332" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 332</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) intr. a) to be roused from sleep, to cease to sleep, to be awakened: <bibl n="shak. luc 219" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 219</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 219" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 219</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 87.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 87, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 148</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 80</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 40.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 40.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 40.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 61</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 61</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 61</bibl> 164 (Qq <emph>stirs</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.155" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 31</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.253" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 253</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.253" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 253</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.7.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 7, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.7.42" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.233" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 233</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.233" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 233</bibl>
<lb />b) to be awake, not to sleep: <bibl n="shak. luc 126" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 126" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 126</bibl> <bibl n="shak. pp 426" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 426</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 209</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 209</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 82.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 19</bibl> <cit><quote>(ne'er was dream so like a --ing).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 56</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.263" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 263</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.227" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 227</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.117" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 4, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.249" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 249</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.43" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.306" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 306</bibl>. With an accus. denoting the effect: <cit><quote>I'll w. mine eyeballs blind first,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 104</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>I'll w. mine eyeballs first</emph>). Metaphorically: <cit><quote>to keep thy sharp woes --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1136" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1136</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all replication prompt . . . for his advantage still did w. and sleep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 123" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 123</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>keep in Tunis, and let Sebastian w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.260" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 260</bibl></cit>.
<lb />== to sit up for amusement, to hold a nightly revel: <cit><quote>for thee watch I whilst thou dost w. elsewhere,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 61.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 61, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the king doth w. to-night and takes his rouse,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 8</bibl></cit>.
